genresAdvancedInfo.name: folk metal latinoamericano
genresAdvancedInfo.description: This is a variation of folk metal that incorporates traditional Latin American folk music. It often features the use of instruments like the charango and quena, as well as lyrics and themes inspired by the region's folklore and history. The result is a fusion of heavy metal and traditional Latin American sounds.
